"Baidu Xiaodu Car OS Privacy Policy You are welcome to use our products and services! We attach great importance to your privacy protection and personal information protection. We try to present this Privacy Policy in a clearer and more understandable way for you to truthfully convey the information we wish to convey to you, and to have a clear understanding of the purpose, possible use, and other aspects of the collection of certain information (which may include your personal information) before you provide us with certain information (which is likely to include your personal information) and allow us to process and share certain information. For your ease of reading and understanding, we have defined the terminology as described in Appendix 1 of this Privacy Policy：definitions\" to understand what these definitions are about. This Privacy Policy is designed to help you understand what data we collect, why we collect it, what we do with it, and how we protect it. If you log in to your Baidu account and use the products and services of Baidu Xiaodu Car OS, it means that you agree with the content we describe in this policy. We will ask for your consent in advance when using your information for purposes not covered by this Privacy Policy. The \"General Provisions of Baidu Privacy Policy\" applies to all products and services of Baidu Group, and if there are any matters not covered by this Privacy Policy, the \"General Provisions of Baidu Privacy Policy\" shall prevail, and if there is any inconsistency between this Privacy Policy and the \"General Provisions of Baidu Privacy Policy\", this Privacy Policy shall prevail. When you use third-party products and services through Baidu Xiaodu Car OS, if you provide your personal information to the third party, your information will be subject to the third party's privacy policy. Please ensure that the personal information you provide to us, and that you authorize us to collect, process, use, store, share, transfer or publicly disclose relevant personal information within the scope described in this Privacy Policy, will not infringe upon the legitimate rights and interests of others. This Privacy Policy will help you understand the following： (1) How we collect and use your personal information (2) How we use cookies and similar technologies (3) How we share, transfer, and publicly disclose your personal information (4) How we store and protect your personal information (5) Your rights (6) How we process the personal information of minors (7) How your personal information is transferred across borders (8) Revisions to the Privacy Policy (9) How to Contact Us We understand the importance of personal information to you, and we also know that providing effective protection for your information is the cornerstone of the healthy and sustainable development of our business. We are committed to maintaining your trust in us, abiding by applicable laws and our commitment to you, and doing our best to ensure the safe and reasonable use of your personal information. At the same time, we solemnly promise that we will take corresponding security protection measures to protect your personal information in accordance with mature security standards in the industry. 1. How we collect and use your personal information Baidu Xiaodu car OS will collect and use your personal information for the following purposes described in this privacy policy： (1) Baidu Xiaodu on-board OS business functions Baidu Xiaodu on-board OSInter-level solution is a full-capacity integrated on-board system-level solution,Released a fusion of human-vehicle voice dialogue、Intelligent navigation、Vehicle-home interconnection (V2H)、Personalized services and content、Vehicle safety and other ecological functions。 In particular,Small car OSThe integration of many car life service functions,For example, smart parking lot、Movie ticket purchase, etc。 (2) To provide you with our products and services In order to provide you with and enable you to obtain better and more personalized products and services, when you use our products and services, we will collect and use your personal information in the following ways： 1. Personal information that you provide directly and that we collect automatically (1) Registration Information. You use Baidu Xiaodu car OSServing,You need to log in to the registered Baidu general account。 When you register a Baidu general account, you need to provide us with at least a username, mobile phone number, and create a password. Baidu Xiaodu car OSThe company may launch operational activities from time to time for newly launched services and functions,If you participate in relevant operational activities,We will collect including but not limited to your identity information、Contact information、Transaction account information through the operation activity interface,In order to get in touch with you,Send you operational rewards, etc。 If you do not participate in the relevant operational activities, you do not need to provide the above information. (2) Device Information. In order to provide better products and/or services and improve user experience, we collect device attribute information (such as your hardware model, operating system version, device configuration, unique device identifier, international mobile device identity code IMEI, network device hardware address MAC, advertising identifier IDFA, etc.), device connection information (telecom operator, language used), and device status information (such as device sensor data, etc.). We may associate information collected from your various devices so that we can provide you with consistent services across those devices. We may associate your device information or phone number with your Baidu account. (3) Log Information. When you use Baidu Xiaodu car OS service, our server will automatically record some information, such as your use of our products and/or services, IP address, language used, abnormal information during using the system, system-related security logs, and the date, time, duration of access to the service, etc. (4) Location Information. We collect and process information about your physical location so that you can access navigation and other location-based services without having to manually enter your geographic coordinates. We use a variety of technologies for location, including IP addresses, GPS, and other sensors that provide relevant information (such as information that may provide us with nearby devices, Wi-Fi access points, and cell towers). (5) Voice messages. Baidu Xiaodu in-vehicle OS provides you with device-based voice recognition capabilities. In order to provide you with more accurate services, you authorize us to send your voice commands to the server, and we will give feedback based on your voice commands. When you activate the small car OSprogram or wake up the small car OSThe device,We will automatically receive and record the audio information generated during your interaction with the device terminal,And use this information to improve the ability of the small car OS to understand the content you express,In order to continuously improve the speed and quality of the recognition and response of the small car OS,Improve the intelligence of the small car OS。 Please note,If the wake-up function of the device or program is turned on,When Xiaodu car OS hears the wake word,She will be woken up,And we will only collect voice information after hearing the wake word。 (6) Vehicles and driving-related information. Baidu Xiaodu on-board OS provides you with restricted traffic inquiry、Smart parking lot、AR navigation and other services related to your specific vehicle and driving route,You need to provide us or authorize us to obtain necessary vehicle information (including but not limited to your vehicle brand、Vehicle model、License plate number、Vehicle identification code、Engine number、Vehicle condition information、Vehicle status、 driving environment, etc.),When the above services are provided to you by a third party connected to Xiaodu vehicle OS,You authorize us to provide the information to the third party that provides you with services。 If you do not provide the above information or the information provided is incorrect, you may not be able to obtain the relevant services or functions, or you may not be able to achieve the intended effect of the relevant services. 2. Information We Indirectly Collect About You (1) Information about your order for third-party products or services. Baidu Xiaodu vehicle OSThe access to a wealth of third-party services (such as smart parking lots, movie ticket purchases, smart homes, etc.). You authorize us to indirectly obtain necessary relevant information from a third party, including but not limited to your order information, in order to facilitate your inquiry in Baidu Xiaodu Vehicle OS. If you refuse us to collect the above information,Please do not use the corresponding Baidu Xiaodu car OSThe relevant third-party functions and services,Your failure to provide relevant information will not affect your use of Baidu Xiaodu car OSThe core business functions。 (3) To display and deliver customized content to you By using the information we collect, we may be able to provide you with customized content, such as search results, feeds, or advertising/promotion results that may be shown or recommended to you that are more relevant than universally pushed. In order to provide you with a better experience, improve our services, or other purposes with your consent, we may use the information collected through certain services for our other services, subject to relevant laws and regulations. (iv) To provide you with security guarantees In order to improve the security of your use of the products and services provided by us and Baidu's affiliates and partners, we may use your information for identity verification, customer service, security prevention, fraud monitoring, credit analysis, etc., to prevent, detect and investigate fraud, endangering security, illegal or violating agreements, policies or rules with us, and to protect the legitimate rights and interests of you, our other users, our or Baidu's affiliates, partners and the public. (5) To improve our products and services, and to conduct internal audits, data analysis, and research We use the collected information to provide and improve the products and services provided by us and Baidu's affiliates and partners, and to carry out necessary business operations, such as operating products or providing services, evaluating, maintaining and improving the performance of products and services, developing new products and services, and providing customer support. In order to improve the products and services of us and Baidu's affiliates and partners, we may also conduct statistics and analysis on the use of products. At the same time, Baidu may share these statistics with the public to show the overall usage trend of our services, but these statistics will not contain any of your identifying information. (6) Other purposes When we want to use the information for other purposes not specified in this Privacy Policy, and use the information collected for a specific purpose for other purposes, we will ask for your consent in advance. 2. How we use cookies and similar technologies To ensure the proper functioning of our website, we store small data files called cookies on your computer or mobile device. Cookies typically contain identifiers, site names, and some numbers and characters. The main function of cookies is to facilitate the use of website products and services, as well as to help the website count the number of unique visitors. Using cookie technology, we are able to provide you with a more thoughtful and personalized service and allow you to set your specific service options. When you use Baidu's products and services, cookies are sent to your device. We allow cookies (or other anonymous identifiers) to be sent to Baidu's servers when you interact with the services we provide to our partners, such as advertising and/or promotional services, and the features of the services provided by Baidu that may be displayed on other websites. We do not use cookies for any purpose other than those described in this Privacy Policy. For details, see AboutCookies.org. III. How We Share, Transfer, and Publicly Disclose Your Personal Information (i) Sharing We will treat your information with a high degree of diligence. Except in the following circumstances, we will not share your information with any company, organization or individual other than Baidu and its affiliates without your consent： 1. After obtaining your explicit consent, we will share your personal information with other parties. We may share your personal information externally in accordance with laws and regulations, or in accordance with the mandatory requirements of competent government departments or judicial rulings. 2. For the purposes stated in this Privacy Policy only, some of our services will be provided by authorized partners. We may share some of your personal information with our partners to provide better customer service and user experience. We will only share your personal information for legal, legitimate, necessary, specific and explicit purposes, and will only share personal information related to the provision of services. Our partners are not authorized to use the shared personal information for any other purpose. Currently, our authorized partners include the following types:： (1) Service Platform or Service Provider. Baidu Xiaodu car OSThe access to a wealth of third-party services。 When you choose to use the third-party service, you authorize us to provide the information necessary to achieve the purpose of the service to the third-party service platform or service provider (for example, when the third party provides you with vehicle-related services such as smart parking lot, it needs to obtain your license plate number and other vehicle information and your contact information) so that it can provide you with the service. (2) Software and hardware/system service providers. When the third-party software and hardware/system products or services are combined with the products or services of Baidu Xiaodu on-board OS to provide you with services,With your authorization,We will provide your necessary personal information to the third-party software and hardware/system service providers,For you to use the service,Or for us to analyze the use of products and services,To improve your experience。 3. Your personal information may be shared with our affiliates in order to facilitate us to jointly provide you with services based on our linked accounts, recommend information that may be of interest to you, or protect the personal and property safety of Baidu's affiliates, other users or the public from infringement. We will only share necessary personal information (for example, we will share your necessary account information with our affiliates in order to facilitate your use of Baidu account to use our affiliates' products and/or services), and if we change the use and processing purpose of personal information, we will seek your authorization and consent again. 4. We will sign strict confidentiality agreements with companies, organizations and individuals with whom we share personal information, requiring them to process personal information in accordance with our instructions, this Privacy Policy and any other relevant confidentiality and security measures. (ii) Assignment We will not transfer your personal information to any company, organization or individual other than Baidu and its affiliates, except in the following circumstances： (1) Obtain your explicit authorization or consent in advance; (2) To meet the requirements of laws, regulations, legal procedures or mandatory government requirements or judicial rulings; (3) If we or our affiliates are involved in a merger, division, liquidation, acquisition or sale of assets or business, etc., and your personal information may be transferred as part of such transaction, we will ensure the confidentiality of such information at the time of transfer and require the new company holding your personal information, The organization continues to be bound by this Privacy Policy, otherwise we will require the company or organization to ask you for authorization and consent again. (3) Public disclosure We will only publicly disclose your personal information under the following circumstances： (1) Obtain your explicit consent; (2) Based on laws and regulations, legal procedures, litigation or mandatory requirements of government authorities. (4) Exceptions to obtaining prior authorization and consent when sharing, transferring, or publicly disclosing personal information In the following circumstances, sharing, transferring, and publicly disclosing your personal information do not require your prior authorization and consent： (1) Directly related to national security and national defense security; (2) Directly related to public safety, public health, or major public interests; (3) In connection with criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and sentencing"
